resources.name: Public API
resources.description:
## Introduction
Welcome to the API documentation for Aimfox! This guide provides all the details you need to integrate seamlessly with our platform. Whether you're building a custom integration, automating workflows, or enhancing your application with our features, this documentation will help you get started quickly and efficiently.

## Authentication
To use the Aimfox API, the first step is to authenticate your requests with an API key. While API keys do not expire, they can be deleted when needed.

To obtain an API key, go to the 'Workspace settings' tab on your Aimfox dashboard, then navigate to the 'Integrations' tab to access your API keys.

Once you have your API key, include it in every request to the Aimfox API. Add the 'Authorization' header to each request and set its value to 'Bearer YOUR\_API\_KEY'.

## Rate Limits
The Aimfox API allows a maximum of **60** requests per minute. All requests are attributed to the same limit.
Going above the limit will return a **429** HTTP status code and an error.




We strive to make your integration experience as seamless as possible. Explore the endpoints, and if you have any questions, suggestions, or need support, feel free to reach out to us at **tech@constel.co**. Happy coding!

---

resources.name: Add Profile to Campaign
resources.description:
This POST request is used to add a specific profile to an Aimfox campaign, using the profiles LinkedIn url.

- **Applicable campaign states:** `ACTIVE`, `PAUSED`, `DONE`, `CREATED`
- **Unsupported campaign types:** `GROUP MESSAGE`, `EVENT MESSAGE`

**Possible error messages:**

```
{
  "blocked": "The Target is Blocked",
  "locked": "The Target is Locked in another Campaign",
  "miningFailed": "The Target was not found",
  "noPFP": "The Target has no Profile Picture",
  "alreadyConnected": "The Target is already a lead",
  "notLead": "The Target is not a lead",
  "closed": "The target cannot receive free InMails"
}
```

```response:200
{
	"status": "ok"
}
```

```response:400
{
	"status": "fail",
	"error": {
		"code": 400,
		"message": "The Target is Locked",
		"type": "Bad Request",
		"data": "locked"
	}
}
```

resources.description:
This POST request is used to start a conversation with an account or group.
If a conversation with a specific recipient exists, a message will be sent to the existing conversation.

#### Disclaimer: Adding multiple recipients does not send individual messages to each recipient. Instead, it creates a group with all the recipients and sends the message to the group.

Available body options:
```
{
	"message": "Example Message",
	"recipients": ["account_id"]
}
```
```
{
	"message": "Example Message",
	"recipient_urns": ["account_urn"]
}
```

```response:200
{
	"conversation_urn": "2-ODk4OGVjNTUtYjczOS00NGNhLTlmMTctMTJjNWI0YThiN2M4XzAxMw==",

}
```
